  "pr_number": 510,
  "issue_number": 488,
  "issue_title": "feat(api): add cursor pagination and total matched counts to registry search",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nThe public registry search endpoint should expose real pagination metadata for API, MCP, and Raycast clients. Right now it slices results to the requested limit and reports the sliced count, which makes clients unable to know whether more matching results exist.\n\n## Current state\n\n- `/api/registry/search` accepts `q`, category/platform/trust filters, and `limit`.\n- The route computes `matched`, slices to `results`, then returns `count: results.length`.\n- There is no `total`, `offset`, `cursor`, or `nextCursor`.\n- MCP `list_category_entries` has offset pagination, but `search_registry` does not expose equivalent paging semantics.\n\n## Desired behavior\n\n- Add pagination metadata without breaking existing clients.\n- Return total matched count separately from returned result count.\n- Support a bounded `offset` or opaque `cursor` for follow-up pages.\n- Keep all validation strict and bounded.\n- Update OpenAPI/API contract tests.\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Extend `registrySearchQuerySchema` with either `offset` or `cursor`; prefer the simplest deterministic option unless cursor encoding is already used elsewhere.\n- Return `count`, `total`, `limit`, and `nextOffset`/`nextCursor`.\n- Keep `results` capped at the existing max response size.\n- Consider mirroring the same shape in MCP search later, or include it in this issue if the shared search helper makes that low-risk.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Clients can request page 2 without repeating local filtering.\n- Response exposes total matched results and returned count distinctly.\n- Facets remain computed against the full matching context, not just the current page.\n- Existing clients that only read `results` and `count` continue working.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm validate:openapi`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run tests/api-contracts.test.ts tests/registry-search-facets.test.ts`\n- Add or update focused unit tests for the touched API/helper surface.\n- Run the narrow relevant validation command for the changed package or route.\n- Run `git diff --check` before opening a PR.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-24T21:31:44.000Z",
